Type Parameters:

public class ActiveArcManager<R extends GrammarRule<T>,T extends Token>
extends java.lang.Object

Handles extending arcs based on incoming Keys and storing partially completed ActiveArcs. All completed arcs are handed off to the Chart.

Author:
Jonathan Clark

Field Detail

DEFAULT_PACKING_SIZE

public static final int DEFAULT_PACKING_SIZE
Initial ArrayList capacity where potential ambiguities may be packed. Increasing this value will take up more memory initially, but will reduce the amount of time spent growing the ambiguity vectors if the number of ambiguities created during parsing typically exceeds this number.

extendArcs

public void extendArcs(Key<R,T> key)
Advance the "dots" that iterates over the source side RHS's of arcs based on a new key. This method is used by ChartParser.parse to extend the arcs using terminals symbols from the input.
